Early Discharge Recommendation

Defendant Jacob M. Metz in court with attorney Shari L Post. Louis J. Molepske appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
10:52 a.m.  Court calls the case. 

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
State files amended information amending Count 3.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.
Atty Post received a copy of the amended information and waives its reading.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
Counts 1, 2 & 3 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty Counts 1, 2 & 3.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Atty Molepske makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Post makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Court questions the defendant re: residence. 

BY THE COURT:
Count 1 
Serve 120 days jail, STAYED
Huber if approved by the jail administration.
Placed on probation for a period of 24 months: 
Pay restitution in the amount of $75 to the Nekoosa Cash Advance.
Pay fine of $200 plus costs including the DNA surcharge. 
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations, if there are any.
Maintain absolute sobriety.
Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.
Do not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid prescription and be taken according to the prescription. 
Sign releases with the agent so they can monitor any prescriptions.
Prescriptions from one pharmacy.
No contact with David Haskins unless he approves in writing, with the exception of a letter of apology.  To be written within 30 days, given to the agent who will forward to the victim. 
Work fulltime, go to school fulltime or a combination thereof. 
Engage in any other counseling deemed appropriate by the agent. 
Court will allow early discharge after he has served 50% of his probation if he is in full compliance and paid off all his financial obligations. 

Counts 2 & 3:
Serve 120 days jail, STAYED, concurrent to one another and concurrent to Count 1
Huber if approved by the jail administration.
Placed on probation for a period of 2 years, concurrent:
Comply with all conditions set forth in Count 1. 
Pay costs including the DNA surcharge. 
Court will allow early discharge after he has served 50% of his probation if he is in full compliance and paid off all his financial obligations. 

There is no jail credit.  
Court advises of postconviction.
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 10, 2015 at 10:30 am.
Pre-trial conference on February 23, 2015 at 11:00 am.
Forward Time Expired.  New notice sent 2/18/15 ks
